hands_on_practices.problem:
Consider three vectors in a three-dimensional Euclidean space, defined in terms of the standard Cartesian basis vectors $\hat{i}$, $\hat{j}$, and $\hat{k}$:
$$
\begin{align*}
\vec{a} &= 2\hat{i} - \hat{j} + 3\hat{k} \\
\vec{b} &= \hat{i} + 4\hat{j} - 2\hat{k} \\
\vec{c} &= -3\hat{i} - 12\hat{j} + 6\hat{k}
\end{align*}
$$
Determine the components of the vector that results from the vector triple product operation $\vec{a} \times (\vec{b} \times \vec{c})$.
